<br>
First of all, all epic information can be found here:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://matt.waggoner.com/orbofmastery.html">matt.waggoner.com/orbofmastery.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Next: The enraged dread wolf isn't that hard to kill solo...and they do wander quite close to the WC zone. This was still high blue at 50, but I killed it with half a bar of mana (heals and nukes) with a 49 fire pet.<br>
<br>
Next: You don't need wolf form in Unrest if you're 51+....sure, some things will aggro, but it's not a big deal. At least, I didn't have a problem with it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Next: Why would you need to get your FV faction up? It's not like the Element of Earth turn in guy is in the city. He wanders the forest (I hear he wanders the cliffs 90% of the time). So don't worry about that FV faction. If you're a DE, I'd worry more about the VS hit you take from killing the good Captain in OT.<br>
<br>
Next: ....um...faction for &quot;that Quilmaine girl for the feathered cloak quest&quot;? The cloak is for the Element of Air quest, and you don't do a quest with Quill, you just kill her and hope she drops the cloak, not the legs. ^_^<br>
<br>
Next: The BB turn-in you can do regardless of dwarf faction - just go invis in case you wander into any guards while you're looking for her/having a tracker look for her.<br>
<br>
Next: Fairie guards in Lfay - they're in a camp, and don't wander. If you're 44+ this camp is a joke. (PS: Go at 51 with Scintillation for some real fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I love pulling about 10 then Scint'ing....you hear all this &quot;Eee! Eee! Eee!&quot; Hehe)<br>
<br>
